Professionals












Jay Wenger
Mr. Wenger is the Managing Director of Susquehanna Group Advisors, Inc. where he oversees the firm’s public finance advisory activities. He joined SGA in 2003 with over 30 years of investment banking and financial advisory experience. Mr. Wenger’s experience includes structuring and executing transactions in the capital markets for a wide range of municipal clients including higher education and health care institutions, school districts, counties, townships, boroughs, municipal authorities and other governmental entities.
Mr. Wenger received a B.A. in Economics from Franklin & Marshall College. Mr. Wenger is a former member of the Central Dauphin School District Board having served on the Finance Committee.










John Hewlett
Mr. Hewlett is a Director with Susquehanna Group Advisors, Inc. where he serves as a municipal advisory professional and manages SGA’s analytics.  Mr. Hewlett joined SGA in 2009 and has over 18 years of investment banking and financial advisory experience.  His experience includes advising a variety of municipal clients on raising debt capital, managing their debt portfolio, refunding debt and implementing various financial products.
Mr. Hewlett received a B.A. in Economics from Colgate University.






 




